PARTIAL STOPPERS:

How do you find out if you and partner each have a ‘partial stopper’ that together stops a suit, 
in order to arrive at a NT contract based on the joint partial stopper?

For example, if one partner has J10x and the other partner has Qx, that suit is stopped, 
but neither partner has a full stopper.

So there is a way to ask partner for a partial stopper in a suit where you have a partial stopper.

Two Rules:   

1.  If partner bids a suit in which he has already denied having a stopper, this shows a half stopper 
and asks partner to bid NT with a half stopper as well.

2.  If a player continues showing stoppers in other suits after BOTH have denied a stopper in one suit,
it shows a half stopper in the denied suit.

If both partners each have a half stopper, that makes a full stopper in that suit, and NT can be bid.

Half stoppers:   J10x, Kx, Qx, Jxxx, K (singleton)
A lot of length in suit can also be considered half a stopper (10xxxxx).


